<text id="A7150T">
<front id="d2">
<div1 type="summary" id="d3">
<p>Scott writes to E. P. Smith about a lost box of books.</p> 
</div1> 
<div1 type="figure" id="d4">
<p>American Missionary Association letterhead</p> 
</div1> 
<div1 type="envelope" id="d5">
<p></p> 
</div1> 
</front> 

<body id="d6">
<div1 type="letter" id="d7">
<head>
<name type="recipient">Rev E P Smith</name> 
<name type="place">Mission Home, Staunton Va</name> 
</head>

<opener>
<dateline>
    <date value="1869-03-08">Mar 8<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1869</date> 
</dateline> 
<salute>Dear Sir</salute> 
</opener> 

<p>I wrote you a few days ago about the lost box of books and rec'd no answer  The Box is marked and directed as follows--as per Invoice.</p>
	<p>NY 13 February 1869 Shipped per Steamer C C Knight Gov't Transportation.  Marked U S John Scott Staunton Va Care Geo Q White Mayor <del rend="none" hand="h1"></del> Richmond Va.</p>

<p>No 3180. 1 Box</p>
	<p>Rev RM Manly Sup Schls Richmond informs me that such St'r does not sail to Richmond.  Thinks it goes to Alexandria.  We are much pressed for books</p>


<closer>
<salute></salute> 
<signed>John Scott</signed> 

<name type="place">New York</name> 
</closer> 
</div1> 
</body> 
</text> 
